FBIS3-17598 "drsov059_b_94024" FBIS-SOV-94-059 Document Type:Daily Report 26 Mar 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Yavlinskiy Considers 1996 Presidential Bid LD2603224094 Moscow 2x2 Television in Russian 2155 GMT 26 Mar 94 LD2603224094 Moscow 2x2 Television Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] Well-known Russian economist Grigoriy Yavlinskiy, the leader of one of the State Duma factions, has said that he is prepared to take part in 1996 presidential election, but on one condition: They should be held in accordance with the law. He announced this on Friday, 25 March at a press conference in Nizhniy Novgorod.
